1.3 ggplot function

  • First argument: data frame
  • Second argument: aes()
ggplot(diamonds, aes())

2 With x in aes() in ggplot()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price))

2.1 geom_hist(): histogram

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) + geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.1.1 new line can be inserted after +

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.1.2 Grouping samples

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price, fill=clarity)) +
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.1.3 Grouping samples (independent histogram)

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price, fill=clarity)) +
  geom_histogram(position = "identity", alpha = 0.8)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.1.4 Grouping samples (dodged histogram)

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price, fill=clarity)) +
  geom_histogram(position = "dodge", alpha = 0.8)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.2 geom_density(): density plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_density()

3 With x and y in aes() in ggplot()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price))

3.1 geom_point: Scatter plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_point()

3.1.1 Change size of points in scatter plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_point(size = 0.5)

3.2 geom_smooth: Draw smoothed line

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=depth, y=price)) + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

3.2.1 geom_point() + geom_smooth

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_point(size = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

3.3 geom_bin2d()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_bin2d()

3.4 geom_boxplot(): box plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=clarity, y=price)) + 
  geom_boxplot()

3.5 geom_violin(): violin plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=clarity, y=price)) + 
  geom_violin()
